The _server_ MUST:
    1. handle a new connection from a client.
    2. relay a message from a client to the rest of the
    clients without relaying back to the author client.
    3. handle the following messages from the _client_:
        1. CONNECT <nickname>
        2. MESSAGE <the message>

The _client_ MUST:
    1. Accept a user alias + server address when it starts.
        1. this would then create a message like "CONNECT
        andre"
    2. Send a message to the server, i.e. "MESSAGE the
    message".
    3. Handle the following commands from the _user_:
        1. /quit -> kills the connection

